\par }{\b\f2\fs20\lang1024\langfe1024\noproof\insrsid9855598 Eye Contact}{\f2\fs20\lang1024\langfe1024\noproof\insrsid9855598 
\par Flush eyes thoroughly with water for several minutes. Remove contact
\par lenses after initial 1-2 minutes and continue flushing for several
\par additional minutes. If effects occur, consult a physician, preferably
\par an ophthalmologist. Consult medical personnel.
\par 
\par }{\b\f2\fs20\lang1024\langfe1024\noproof\insrsid9855598 Ingestion}{\f2\fs20\lang1024\langfe1024\noproof\insrsid9855598 
\par Seek medical attention immediately.
\par 
\par }{\b\f2\fs20\lang1024\langfe1024\noproof\insrsid9855598 Note to Physician}{\f2\fs20\lang1024\langfe1024\noproof\insrsid9855598 
\par No specific antidote. Treatment of exposure should be directed at the
\par control of symptoms and the clinical condition of the patient.
\par 
\par ________________________________________________________________________
\par }{\b\f2\fs20\lang1024\langfe1024\noproof\insrsid9855598 5. FIRE-FIGHTING MEASURES}{\f2\fs20\lang1024\langfe1024\noproof\insrsid9855598 
\par 
\par }{\b\f2\fs20\lang1024\langfe1024\noproof\insrsid9855598 Extinguishing Media}{\f2\fs20\lang1024\langfe1024\noproof\insrsid9855598 
\par Water fog or fine spray. Carbon dioxide. Alcohol resistant foam. Dry
\par chemical fire extinguishers.
\par 
\par }{\b\f2\fs20\lang1024\langfe1024\noproof\insrsid9855598 Hazardous Combustion Products}{\f2\fs20\lang1024\langfe1024\noproof\insrsid9855598 
\par Combustion products may include and are not limited to: Carbon oxides.
\par Incomplete combustion may lead to the build-up of toxic pyrolysis
\par products.
\par 
\par }{\b\f2\fs20\lang1024\langfe1024\noproof\insrsid9855598 Protection of Firefighters}{\f2\fs20\lang1024\langfe1024\noproof\insrsid9855598 
\par Wear positive-pressure, self-contained breathing apparatus.
\par 
\par }{\b\f2\fs20\lang1024\langfe1024\noproof\insrsid9855598 Specific Fire or Explosion Hazards}{\f2\fs20\lang1024\langfe1024\noproof\insrsid9855598 
\par Will support combustion.
\par 
\par }{\b\f2\fs20\lang1024\langfe1024\noproof\insrsid9855598 Specific Methods of Firefighting}{\f2\fs20\lang1024\langfe1024\noproof\insrsid9855598 
\par Fire debris must be disposed of in accordance with local regulations.
\par Do not discharge extinguishing waters into streams, rivers and lakes.
\par 
\par ________________________________________________________________________
\par }{\b\f2\fs20\lang1024\langfe1024\noproof\insrsid9855598 6. ACCIDENTAL RELEASE MEASURES}{\f2\fs20\lang1024\langfe1024\noproof\insrsid9855598 
\par 
\par }{\b\f2\fs20\lang1024\langfe1024\noproof\insrsid9855598 Personal Precautions}{\f2\fs20\lang1024\langfe1024\noproof\insrsid9855598 
\par Wear adequate personal protective equipment, see Section 8, EXPOSURE
\par CONTROLS/PERSONAL PROTECTION. Spills may cause very slippery surfaces.
\par 
\par }{\b\f2\fs20\lang1024\langfe1024\noproof\insrsid9855598 Environmental Precautions}{\f2\fs20\lang1024\langfe1024\noproof\insrsid9855598 
\par Dike to prevent contamination of ground and surface water, then
\par transfer into closed containers. Recover if possible, or dispose of
\par according to applicable regulations, see Section 13, DISPOSAL
\par CONSIDERATIONS.
\par 
