\par }{\b\f2\fs20\lang1024\langfe1024\noproof\insrsid9855598 Methods of Cleaning Up}{\f2\fs20\lang1024\langfe1024\noproof\insrsid9855598 
\par Spills should be contained by, and covered with large quantities of
\par sand, earth or any other readily available absorbent material which is
\par then brushed in vigorously to assist absorption. The mixture can then
\par be collected into drums and removed for disposal. Wash area from
\par residues with soap and water and rinse down. Contaminated water should
\par be retained, not being allowed to flow into ground or surface water.
\par 
\par ________________________________________________________________________
\par }{\b\f2\fs20\lang1024\langfe1024\noproof\insrsid9855598 7. HANDLING AND STORAGE}{\f2\fs20\lang1024\langfe1024\noproof\insrsid9855598 
\par 
\par }{\b\f2\fs20\lang1024\langfe1024\noproof\insrsid9855598 Handling}{\f2\fs20\lang1024\langfe1024\noproof\insrsid9855598 
\par Since polyols are handled together with diisocyanates, proper
\par distinction between these two kinds of products is essential in order
\par to avoid undesired mixing resulting in uncontrolled polymerisation.
\par 
\par }{\b\f2\fs20\lang1024\langfe1024\noproof\insrsid9855598 Storage}{\f2\fs20\lang1024\langfe1024\noproof\insrsid9855598 
\par Keep container tightly closed; product is hygroscopic.
\par 
\par }{\b\f2\fs20\lang1024\langfe1024\noproof\insrsid9855598 - Storage Temperature and Shelf-Life}{\f2\fs20\lang1024\langfe1024\noproof\insrsid9855598 
\par Store between 15 and 25 deg.C. Shelf life is 6 months.
\par 
\par ________________________________________________________________________
\par }{\b\f2\fs20\lang1024\langfe1024\noproof\insrsid9855598 8. EXPOSURE CONTROLS/PERSONAL PROTECTION}{\f2\fs20\lang1024\langfe1024\noproof\insrsid9855598 
\par 
\par }{\b\f2\fs20\lang1024\langfe1024\noproof\insrsid9855598 Exposure Guidelines}{\f2\fs20\lang1024\langfe1024\noproof\insrsid9855598 
\par None established for the preparation.
\par 
\par }{\b\f2\fs20\lang1024\langfe1024\noproof\insrsid9855598 Engineering Controls}{\f2\fs20\lang1024\langfe1024\noproof\insrsid9855598 
\par Good general ventilation should be sufficient for most conditions.
\par 
\par }{\b\f2\fs20\lang1024\langfe1024\noproof\insrsid9855598 Personal Protective Equipment}{\f2\fs20\lang1024\langfe1024\noproof\insrsid9855598 
\par 
\par }{\b\f2\fs20\lang1024\langfe1024\noproof\insrsid9855598 Respiratory Protection}{\f2\fs20\lang1024\langfe1024\noproof\insrsid9855598 
\par For most conditions, no respiratory protection is needed; however, if
\par handling at elevated temperature without sufficient ventilation or in
\par presence of aerosols, use an approved air-purifying respirator.
\par 
\par }{\b\f2\fs20\lang1024\langfe1024\noproof\insrsid9855598 Skin Protection}{\f2\fs20\lang1024\langfe1024\noproof\insrsid9855598 
\par Wear gloves made of: PVC. Break-through time not established. Discard
\par immediately after contamination.
\par Wear clean, long-sleeved, body-covering clothing. After work and before
\par eating, drinking or smoking wash and clean yourself carefully with soap
\par and water. Contaminated clothing should be washed and/or dry cleaned
\par before re-use.
\par 
\par }{\b\f2\fs20\lang1024\langfe1024\noproof\insrsid9855598 Eye/Face Protection}{\f2\fs20\lang1024\langfe1024\noproof\insrsid9855598 
\par Use safety glasses.
\par 
